# Secrets — CRITICAL (D-12). Never commit real credentials.
.env
*.env
.env.*
!.env.example
kaggle.json
**/kaggle.json
access_token
**/access_token

# Data + heavy artifacts (D-12)
data/

# Transient Kaggle CLI error dumps (D-11) — a failed call's raw stdout/stderr may
# embed a token-shaped string; NEVER commit it. Provenance JSON under control/raw/
# (competition-pages.json, cv-evidence.json) stays TRACKED (D-03) — only this
# transient .txt dump is ignored.
control/raw/last-error.txt

# Phase 3 experiment artifacts — declared now so .gitignore isn't rewritten later (D-13)
experiments/*/artifacts/
# NOTE (Phase 5, CONSCIOUS DECISION — not an accident): `experiments/*/*.csv` sweeps up
# `submission.csv`, and it STAYS IGNORED BY DESIGN — deliberately NO un-ignore negation is
# added for it below. Rationale:
#   - a submission CSV is a HEAVY, DERIVED artifact — same class as data/, *.npy, artifacts/;
#   - provenance is preserved BETTER by the `file_sha256` recorded in control/submissions.jsonl
#     (D-11 requires it anyway), which proves exactly WHICH BYTES were uploaded — a tracked copy
#     of the CSV proves less and costs more;
#   - reproducibility is preserved by the TRACKED experiment.py + seed + git_commit.
# ⚠ If a rule here is ever added/changed, editing this template does NOT update an
# already-scaffolded workspace — `kaggle_gateway._append_line_if_absent` is the retrofit mechanism.
experiments/*/*.csv
experiments/*/*.zip
experiments/*/*.pkl
experiments/*/*.parquet
# Phase 4 kernel-path artifacts — pulled kernel output is FLAT (result.json + oof.npy
# + rendered .ipynb) so heavy binaries land at the experiment root, not under
# artifacts/. Ignore the numpy dump and the (untrusted, possibly large/token-shaped)
# execution log; keep the small kernel_run.json provenance TRACKED (D-03/D-14).
experiments/*/*.npy
experiments/*/kernel_log.txt
# Phase 5 submission record: control/submissions.jsonl is TRACKED BY DESIGN — no rule covers it,
# and none should. It is small, diffable, append-only git-backed provenance (exp_id, kaggle_ref,
# file_sha256, status, scores) — the same posture as control/raw/*.json (Phase 2 D-03). It is the
# canonical LB record and the ONLY place an LB score is written (meta.json is immutable — D-11).
# Tracked-but-anticipated exceptions: keep experiment code + meta.json (Phase 3) and
# the kernel_run.json provenance (Phase 4)
!experiments/*/*.py
!experiments/*/*.ipynb
!experiments/*/meta.json
!experiments/*/kernel_run.json

# Python
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.egg-info/
.venv/
